"title": "4416: branch",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4416",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The limb of a tree. The term is used literally, symbolically and metaphorically in Scripture. Branches are personified at times and the Messiah is referred to as the Branch.</p>\n<h2>Branches of various trees</h2>\n<h3>Vine branches</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:22\">GEN 49:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:23\">NUM 13:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa18:5\">ISA 18:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:10\">JER 5:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:9\">JER 6:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:32\">JER 48:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:5-Ezek17:8\">EZK 17:5–17:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek19:10-Ezek19:14\">EZK 19:10–19:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:5-John15:6\">JHN 15:5–15:6</a></p>\n<h3>Olive branches</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:20\">DEU 24:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:14-Neh8:16\">NEH 8:14–8:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:16\">JER 11:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech4:12\">ZEC 4:12</a></p>\n<h3>Palm branches</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:9\">REV 7:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:15\">NEH 8:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:14\">ISA 9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:15\">ISA 19:15</a></p>\n<h3>Branches of other trees</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:11\">JER 1:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:37-Gen30:39\">GEN 30:37–30:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:15\">NEH 8:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:22-Ezek17:23\">EZK 17:22–17:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek31:3\">EZK 31:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:19\">HEB 9:19</a></p>\n<h2>Branches cut down for Jesus Christ's triumphal entry into Jerusalem</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:7-Matt21:9\">MAT 21:7–21:9</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:7-Mark11:10\">MRK 11:7–11:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:12-John12:13\">JHN 12:12–12:13</a></p>\n<h2>Branches providing shelter</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:31-Matt13:32\">MAT 13:31–13:32</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:18-Luke13:19\">LUK 13:18–13:19</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek31:3-Ezek31:14\">EZK 31:3–31:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:10-Dan4:14\">DAN 4:10–4:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:20-Dan4:22\">DAN 4:20–4:22</a></p>\n<h2>The symbolic use of branches</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:11-Jer1:12\">JER 1:11–1:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:14-Isa9:15\">ISA 9:14–9:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:13-Isa19:15\">ISA 19:13–19:15</a></p>\n<h2>Branches in visions</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen40:9-Gen40:13\">GEN 40:9–40:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech4:1-Zech4:14\">ZEC 4:1–4:14</a></p>\n<h2>The metaphorical use of branches</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job29:19\">JOB 29:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:22\">GEN 49:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:32-Job15:35\">JOB 15:32–15:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job18:5-Job18:16\">JOB 18:5–18:16</a></p>\n<h2>The personification of branches</h2>\n<h3>In general</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:5-John15:6\">JHN 15:5–15:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:11-Rom11:24\">ROM 11:11–11:24</a></p>\n<h3>The Messiah as the Branch</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:5\">JER 23:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa4:2\">ISA 4:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:1-Isa11:5\">ISA 11:1–11:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:15-Jer33:16\">JER 33:15–33:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:8\">ZEC 3:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech6:12-Zech6:13\">ZEC 6:12–6:13</a></p>\n<h2>The branches of the lampstand in the tabernacle</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:31-Exod25:32\">EXO 25:31–25:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:35-Exod25:36\">EXO 25:35–25:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:17-Exod37:22\">EXO 37:17–37:22</a></p>",
